What you need to know:

Ochola on Tuesday stood his ground.  “He wrote to StarTimes, which has no contract with Gor Mahia, while the federation recognises my signature. The deal is sealed and since not all Gor Mahia matches would be broadcast by StarTimes, we are looking at how we can make revenue from those that are broadcast,” Ochola said yesterday.He revealed that the federation had given Gor Mahia Sh3 million to help in their preparation for the Caf Champions League preliminary round return leg against APR on Saturday. Gor trail 1-2 following their defeat in Kigali last Saturday.